<doc id="913869" wikidata="Q162928" url="?curid=913869" title="Peganum">
<text>Peganum L. is a genus under the recently separated family Nitrariaceae. Formerly it used to be included in the family Zygophyllaceae.

==Phylogeny and Species==
The genus has around five species, occurring in warm temperate to subtropical regions across the world:
* &quot;Peganum harmala&quot; (Harmal or Syrian rue) — Mediterranean region east to China
* &quot;Peganum mexicanum&quot; — Mexico
* &quot;Peganum multisectum&quot; — China, Mongolia
* &quot;Peganum nigellastrum&quot; — China
* &quot;Peganum texanum&quot; — southern North America

